The U.S. changed the rules for obtaining a visa 
The person must present themselves before their interview at the consulate for the service points for the visa application process, costs will be reduced waiting times. 
From the 10th January 2011 changed the procedures for applying for a visa at the Embassy of the United States and the consulates. 
In the new process, most applicants have prior to their interview at the consulate for the service agencies for visa application (ASC, the first letter in English) to present. 
The staff of the ASC receives the biometric data of the applicant provided by the Consulate checked prior to the interview. 
The new method has certain advantages for the aspirants, including the following: 
decrease the total cost for processing the visa, because it is no longer necessary, the appointment, the processing of visa applications and the transport service, with which the document is issued to pay separately. 
The applicant makes a single payment covering the three services. 
The current price is unchanged: the Gegenwerit to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, $ 150 for visas with the request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors. 
Those who wish to extend their visa only have to lead a discussion at the consulate, they need only imagine the nearest ASC, where they submit their documents and their fingerprints taken. 
Since the biometric data will be collected in the ASC remain, applicants who need a second appointment for the interview at the consulate, there is less time than before. 
Those applying for the visa at the consulates in Ciudad Juarez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo have to pay more to service charge of 26 dollars. 
Additional information about the new procedures for visa application, see the following Web site: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html 
